	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My SuperCard cart turned up today but I'm not having much luck with it.
<br />
<br />I can build a PocketNES GBA ROM (using "Thingy") and it runs fine in VirtualBoyAdvance (though I do get a "A BIOS file is needed" error but it doesn't seem to care?).
<br />
<br />However, copying this to an SD-&gt;SuperCard and putting it in a GBA doesn't seem to work.
<br />
<br />I get the SuperCard menu and the GBA ROM I built appears but I just get a black screen. Bizarrely you can still access the PocketNES menus (pressing both shoulder buttons on the GBA).
<br />
<br />So I thought I'd try just putting a game ROM on the card to make sure it's working OK. I loaded up "Mother 3" (Japanese) and you get the loading progress but on completion, white screen and it hangs.
<br />
<br /><img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />
<br />
<br />Any ideas?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
